IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO SUPPORT THE GRAIN AND FEED INDUSTRY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO ADVOCATE A GLOBAL OPEN MARKET ENVIRONMENT TO EFFICIENTLY PRODUCE AND PROVIDE A SAFE, ABUNDANT, AFFORDABLE, SUSTAINABLE AND WHOLESOME SUPPLY OF GRAIN, OILSEEDS, FEED AND RELATED PRODUCTS RESPONSIVE TO MARKET DEMAND. THE NGFA FOCUSES ON MEMBER INTERESTS THROUGH REPRESENTATION, TRAINING, COMMUNICATION AND EDUCATION TO MEMBERS, GOVERNMENT AND THE PUBLIC.
IRS990.Desc: THE NATIONAL GRAIN AND FEED ASSOCIATION PROVIDES EXPERTISE AND PRACTICAL EXPERIENCE IN FORMULATING POSITIONS AND TRAINING ON ISSUES CONFRONTING THE INDUSTRY, THE DIVERSITY OF INDIVIDUALS, AND THEIR RESPECTIVE BUSINESSES THAT COMPRISE THE COMMITTEES, ENSURES THAT THE POLICIES DEVELOPED ARE REPRESENTATIVE OF THE OVERALL MEMBERSHIP AND BENEFIT A BROAD CROSS SECTION OF THE INDUSTRY.

Form990PartVIISectionAGrp.PersonNm: TODD E KEMP EXEC DIRECTOR OF

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: TRAVEL IS PROVIDED BY THE ORGANIZATION FOR THE PRESIDENT'S SPOUSE FOR MEETINGS. FOR ALL OTHER EMPLOYEES, TRAVEL FOR THEIR PARTNERS IS PROVIDED TO AT LEAST ONE MEETING ANNUALLY.
BONUSES ARE APPROVED BY THE ELECTED OFFICERS AND ARE BASED ON MERIT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL BE A STANDING BOARD COMMITTEE, WHICH SHALL HAVE GENERAL CHARGE OF THE AFFAIRS OF THIS CORPORATION, ACTING IN THE NAME OF THE BOARD WHEN THE BOARD IS NOT IN SESSION, EXCEPT WHERE SUCH ACTION IS RESERVED EXCLUSIVELY TO THE BOARD BY THE ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION OF THE CORPORATION, THESE BYLAWS, OR BY LAW. THE DESIGNATION OF AND THE DELEGATION OF AUTHORITY TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL NOT OPERATE TO RELIEVE THE BOARD, OR ANY INDIVIDUAL DIRECTOR, OF ANY RESPONSIBILITY VESTED IN THEM UNDER THESE BYLAWS OR IMPOSED UPON THEM BY LAW.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: JEREMY AND KAYLA BURKHART HAD A FAMILIAL RELATIONSHIP.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ASSOCIATION HAS MEMBERS, WHICH ARE DIVIDED INTO SIX CLASSES: (1) ACTIVE MEMBERS; (2) TRANSPORTATION MEMBERS; (3) ALLIED MEMBERS; (4) ASSOCIATE MEMBERS; (5) AFFILIATED ASSOCIATION MEMBERS; AND (6) HONORARY MEMBERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH ACTIVE MEMBER, AFFILIATED ASSOCIATION MEMBER, AND ALLIED MEMBER IS ENTITLED TO ONE VOTE AT REGULAR MEETINGS AND FOR ELECTION OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CHANGES TO THE BYLAWS AND TRADE RULES ARE VOTED ON AND APPROVED BY THE MEMBERSHIP AFTER APPROVAL BY THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS PROVIDED TO THE TREASURER FOR REVIEW. THE FORM 990 IS THEN FORWARDED TO THE ENTIRE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, WHO ARE GIVEN A PERIOD OF TIME TO RESPOND IF THEY HAVE QUESTIONS. THE RETURN IS THEN SIGNED BY AN OFFICER OF THE ORGANIZATION BEFORE BEING FILED WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION PAID TO THE PRESIDENT IS DETERMINED BY AN INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION CONSULTANT WHO USES OTHER FORM 990S IN THEIR REVIEW AND ANALYSIS. THIS WAS LAST PERFORMED IN JANUARY 2023. THE CONSULTANT PROVIDES INPUT ON THE OTHER OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES COMPENSATION, BUT COMPENSATION FOR OTHER OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES IS APPROVED BY THE PRESIDENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ASSOCIATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, POLICIES, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
THE ORGANIZATION HAS NOT CHANGED ITS OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT OR SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT AUDITOR PROCESSES DURING THE TAX YEAR.

THE ORGANIZATION HAS AN OPERATING AGREEMENT WITH NORTH AMERICAN EXPORT GRAIN ASSOCIATION, INC. ("NAEGA"), WHICH THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES NAEGA WITH CERTAIN ASSOCIATION SERVICES AND IS REIMBURSED FOR THOSE ON A MONTHLY BASIS. THE REIMBURSEMENTS INCLUDE PAYMENTS FOR SALARIES. THE ORGANIZATION, AS THE REPORTING AGENT, HAS NOT LISTED THE NUMBER OF EMPLOYEES AND THOSE W-2S THAT WERE REPORTED BY NAEGA ON THEIR FORM 990.
